## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Quality tier display language**: Your research says the tier should describe *what has happened to the content*, not just a quality word. For example:
> - "Draft — Recently published, community review pending"  
> - "Developing — 3 edits accepted, no independent review"
> - "Good Article — Independently reviewed by @username, meets editorial standards"
>
> Should we include this level of detail, or keep it simpler?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **72h acceptance window**: The `acceptEdit()` function with lazy evaluation will process old edits when pages load. This means edits might not be marked "accepted" at exactly 72h — it could be 73h or 80h depending on when someone visits the page. Is this acceptable, or do you need precise timing?

